# Knowledge-Graph — Cursor project rules

Last reviewed: 2026-04-15

Canonical agent instructions: **[AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md)** (Knowledge-Graph MCP rules, monorepo commands, Cursor Cloud notes). **[CLAUDE.md](../CLAUDE.md)** adds Claude Code-specific notes and points back to AGENTS.md for Knowledge-Graph.

## Non-negotiables (always apply)

- NEVER edit a function/class/method without running `knowledge-graph_impact` first.
- NEVER rename symbols with find-and-replace — use `knowledge-graph_rename`.
- NEVER commit without running `knowledge-graph_detect_changes()`.
- NEVER ignore HIGH/CRITICAL risk warnings from impact analysis.
- NEVER run `npx knowledge-graph analyze` without `--embeddings` if `.knowledge-graph/meta.json` shows stored embeddings.

Full rules: **[AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md)** (`knowledge-graph:start` block, Cursor Cloud section).

**Rule architecture:** Prefer this file plus optional `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` globs (YAML `globs` in frontmatter). Legacy `.cursorrules` is deprecated; content lives here.
